cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with the problem of computing the flip distance between triangulations, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper involves dynamic programming and uses techniques from graph theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also mentions that the problem is fixed-parameter tractable, which could place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
